0for%20the%20doctor's%20rape%20and%20murder.%20A%20special%20police%20team%20will%20be%20present%20to%20ensure%20the%20family's%20safety%20during%20the%20protest.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22SANJIB%20CHAKRABORTY%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fkolkata%2Fkolkata-rape-murder-victims-parents-to-join-rg-kar-protest-on-eve-of-sc-hearing%2Farticleshow%2F113040160.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Crop%20loss%20is%20a%20huge%20problem%20for%20sustainability%20and%20food%20security.%20I'm%20using%20AI%20and%20computer%20vision%20to%20help%20fix%20it.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20collage%20of%20Valeria%20Kogan%2C%20surrounded%20by%20AI%20patterns%2C%20Farmer%20with%20tablet%20and%20colorful%20gradients%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d74af41d8d2deb96b843d8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EAron%20Su%CC%88veg%3B%20Getty%20Images%3B%20Alyssa%20Powell%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EValeria%20Kogan%20is%20the%20CEO%20of%20Fermata%2C%20a%20software-development%20company%20specializing%20in%20agriculture.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHer%20team%20develops%20AI%20tools%20to%20reduce%20crop%20loss%20that%20causes%20food%20waste%20and%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThis%20article%20is%20part%20of%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbuild-it%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBuild%20IT%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20series%20about%20digital-tech%20trends%20disrupting%20industries.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Valeria%20Kogan%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Fermata.%20The%20company%20develops%20software%20for%20monitoring%20plants%20and%20crops.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20think%20about%20food%20waste%2C%20we%20usually%20think%20on%20the%20scale%20of%20not%20finishing%20our%20lunch.%20In%20reality%2C%20agricultural%20waste%20is%20a%20much%20bigger%20problem.%20An%20estimated%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cabi.org%2Fprojects%2Fglobal-burden-of-crop-loss%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E20%25%20to%2040%25%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20crops%20are%20lost%20to%20pests%20and%20diseases%2C%20which%20affects%20our%20food%20systems%20and%20the%20planet%3B%20greenhouse-gas%20emissions%20from%20food%20that%20is%20never%20eaten%20account%20for%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fourworldindata.org%2Ffood-waste-emissions%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E6%25%20of%20total%20emissions%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20knew%20none%20of%20this%20about%20five%20years%20ago.%20I%20was%20working%20in%20bioinformatics%2C%20developing%20an%20AI-based%20platform%20that%20assists%20oncologists%20in%20diagnosing%20cancer%2C%20and%20I%20knew%20so%20little%20about%20agriculture%20that%20I%20couldn't%20even%20keep%20a%20houseplant%20alive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20someone%20who%20ran%20a%20commercial%20greenhouse%20reached%20out%20to%20discuss%20how%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-iot-technology-make-wine-sustainable-vineyard-practices-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20could%20solve%20those%20crop-loss%20challenges%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20quickly%20saw%20the%20opportunity%20to%20translate%20my%20work%20in%20caring%20for%20human%20health%20into%20caring%20for%20plant%20health%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fermata.tech%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFermata%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20born.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f06a4c78-ade3-45c1-bad9-cba49e234347%5C%22%3EUsing%20AI%20and%20computer%20vision%20where%20humans%20fail%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%2C%20many%20farmers%20try%20to%20detect%20pests%20and%20diseases%20early%20by%20sending%20workers%20into%20the%20fields%20daily%20to%20look%20at%20every%20leaf%20on%20every%20plant%20for%20early%20signs%20of%20issues.%20But%20people%20get%20tired%2C%20get%20distracted%2C%20and%20overlook%20the%20tiny%20changes%20that%20suggest%20an%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20reminded%20me%20of%20the%20specialists%20who%20review%20X-rays%20all%20day%20and%20miss%20early%20signs%20of%20cancer.%20We%20were%20using%20AI%20analysis%20of%20imagery%20to%20solve%20that%20problem%2C%20and%20I%20felt%20the%20same%20solution%20could%20apply%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20we%20thought%20about%20building%20a%20robot%20that%20would%20move%20through%20the%20fields%20but%20realized%20we%20didn't%20have%20the%20expertise%20to%20achieve%20that%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20a%20simpler%20solution%20existed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20developed%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcroptimus.fermata.tech%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECroptimus%20platform%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20uses%20standard%20security%20cameras%20in%20greenhouses%20and%20fields%20to%20take%20pictures%20of%20every%20single%20plant%20several%20times%20a%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20artificial%20intelligence%20processes%20these%20images%20to%20detect%20any%20abnormalities.%20If%20it%20does%2C%20it%20notifies%20farmers%20via%20our%20app%20and%20suggests%20what%20it%20thinks%20the%20issue%20is.%20Using%20data%20science%2C%20we%20can%20also%20provide%20an%20overview%20of%20what's%20going%20on%20in%20a%20facility%20at%20large%2C%20whether%20problems%20are%20increasing%20or%20decreasing%2C%20and%20whether%20treatments%20are%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20this%20technology%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fagtech-agriculture-industry-farming-methods-climate-change-labor-solutions-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efarmers%20need%20less%20labor%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20can%20identify%20issues%20sooner%20than%20they%20would%20with%20humans%2C%20meaning%20they%20can%20apply%20fewer%20pesticides.%20This%20saves%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20and%20helps%20produce%20more%20sustainable%20and%20healthy%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221079%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20interface%20shows%20Fermata%20software%20analyzing%20a%20leaf%20miner%20plant%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c502875da406397bf75f68%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22785%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFermata's%20software%20uses%20imaging%20to%20evaluate%20a%20plant's%20health%20and%20detect%20any%20issues.%3Cp%3EFermata%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223d6dbcc8-bb64-4c3b-9ee3-7cb9fd45055b%5C%22%3EDoing%20things%20manually%20while%20we%20build%20the%20dataset%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20challenges%20we%20had%20to%20overcome%20was%20establishing%20ground%20truth%20to%20build%20a%20reliable%20dataset%20to%20train%20our%20models.%20Every%20agronomist%2C%20or%20crop%20scientist%2C%20has%20their%20own%20opinion%20and%20will%20make%20mistakes%20as%20well.%20We%20needed%20to%20not%20only%20compile%20a%20decent%20dataset%20from%20the%20ground%20up%20but%20also%20build%20machine-learning%20models%20that%20could%20adapt%20to%20mistakes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20did%20a%20few%20things%20to%20help.%20First%2C%20we%20built%20a%20research%20lab%2C%20where%20we%20grow%20plants%2C%20infest%20them%20with%20different%20things%2C%20and%20record%20them%20on%20videos.%20We%20also%20hired%20an%20in-house%20team%20of%20agronomists%20to%20help%20us%20label%20these%20images.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20we%20launched%20our%20product%20to%20the%20public%20before%20it%20was%20automated%2C%20doing%20identifications%20manually%20and%20encouraging%20farmers%20on%20the%20app%20to%20give%20us%20feedback.%20This%20helps%20us%20better%20understand%20the%20problem%20and%20gives%20us%20a%20more%20robust%20dataset.%20Even%20as%20we've%20shifted%20to%20relying%20on%20AI%20for%20identification%2C%20this%20feedback%20loop%20helps%20us%20continually%20improve%20our%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223352e758-ad33-4e8b-830a-d008ed99432c%5C%22%3EBuilding%20relationships%20to%20find%20future%20possibilities%20for%20the%20technology%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20so%20important%20that%20any%20technologist%20trying%20to%20solve%20a%20problem%20in%20a%20new-to-them%20industry%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20more%20conservative%20fields%20like%20agriculture%20%E2%80%94%20stay%20humble%20and%20develop%20real%20relationships%20with%20the%20people%20they're%20hoping%20to%20help.%20If%20I%20marched%20in%20as%20a%20tech-industry%20outsider%20and%20told%20these%20farmers%20who%20have%20been%20doing%20this%20for%20decades%20that%20I%20could%20teach%20them%20how%20to%20operate%20and%20be%20more%20efficient%2C%20it%20wouldn't%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20I%20work%20on%20building%20relationships%20and%20trust%20within%20the%20industry.%20I%20approach%20it%20from%20the%20perspective%20of%20wanting%20to%20learn%20from%20my%20customers%20and%20understand%20how%20my%20tech%20knowledge%20can%20help%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20this%20has%20helped%20me%20see%20even%20more%20potential%20in%20what%20we're%20doing.%20I've%20learned%20that%20there's%20so%20much%20visual%20data%20in%20farming%2C%20from%20understanding%20whether%20bees%20are%20pollinating%20to%20seeing%20how%20employees%20are%20treating%20plants.%20The%20vision%20that%20Fermata%20has%20is%20to%20build%20a%20new%20visual-data%20layer%20in%20the%20agricultural%20industry%20that%20helps%20all%20stakeholders%20%E2%80%94%20from%20farmers%20to%20people%20who%20sell%20fertilizer%20to%20pesticide%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20be%20more%20efficient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22h