%20Ukrainian%20soldier%20walks%20past%20a%20car%20in%20a%20ruined%20neighborhood.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d7449314a5cd1fcc8cbb31%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225143%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Ukrainian%20soldier%20walks%20past%20a%20car%20in%20Sudzha%2C%20in%20Russia's%20Kursk%20region%2C%20in%20August%202024.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20could%20not%20independently%20verify%20Syrskyi's%20figure%2C%20but%20US%20officials%20have%20previously%20confirmed%20the%20movement%20of%20Russian%20troops%20to%20Kursk%20from%20other%20areas%20of%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConflict%20analysts%20at%20the%20Institute%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20War%20think%20tank%20said%20Russia%20may%20have%20sent%20a%20limited%20force%20initially%20intended%20to%20reinforce%20the%20Pokrovsk%20advance%20to%20Kursk.%20However%2C%20these%20forces%20did%20not%20appear%20to%20have%20been%20engaged%20in%20front-line%20operations%2C%20and%20Moscow%20has%20primarily%20redeployed%20troops%20from%20the%20lower-priority%20areas%20of%20the%20front%20line%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Russian%20military%20command%20likely%20remains%20extremely%20averse%20to%20pulling%20combat%20effective%20units%20from%20frontline%20areas%26quot%3B%20in%20places%20like%20Pokrovsk%20and%20Toretsk%2C%20a%20nearby%20city%20under%20similar%20pressure%2C%20the%20ISW%20analysts%20wrote%20in%20a%20Saturday%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.understandingwar.org%2Fbackgrounder%2Frussian-offensive-campaign-assessment-august-31-2024%3Futm_source%3DDaily%2520on%2520Defense%252009032024_09%2F03%2F2024%26utm_medium%3Demail%26utm_campaign%3DWEX_Daily%2520on%2520Defense%26rid%3D25220295%26env%3D3c04aa47499639f882777c7572765d93c4ff544763642577c070df1626ff45f7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eassessment%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20redeployed%20units%20were%20likely%20reserve%20units%20th