d7b0-4651-b076-4c1d0555383b%5C%22%3EKursk%20has%20still%20left%20Putin%20in%20a%20bind%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20shocking%20Kursk%20invasion%20has%20so%20far%20failed%20to%20slow%20the%20Russian%20advances%20around%20Pokrovsk%2C%20it%20has%20still%20produced%20some%20significant%20and%20positive%20results%20for%20Ukraine%20in%20just%20under%20a%20month's%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20controls%20around%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkyivindependent.com%2Fukraine-captures-more-5-square-kilometers-of-territory-in-russias-kursk-oblast-syrskyi-says%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1%2C290%20square%20kilometers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20roughly%20500%20square%20miles%2C%20of%20Russian%20territory%20in%20Kursk%20and%20some%20100%20settlements%20within%20that%20area%2C%20according%20to%20Syrskyi.%20It%20is%20the%20biggest%20attack%20on%20Russian%20soil%20by%20a%20foreign%20enemy%20since%20World%20War%20II.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20continue%20to%20replenish%20the%20exchange%20fund%20for%20Ukraine%20and%20push%20the%20war%20into%20Russian%20territory%2C%26quot%3B%20Ukrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%20said%20over%20the%20weekend%2C%20repeating%20a%20line%20he%20has%20said%20a%20few%20times%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225040%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Destroyed%20Russian%20military%20vehicles%20in%20a%20field.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d7456a14a5cd1fcc8cbb94%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223360%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDestroyed%20Russian%20military%20vehicles%20on%20the%20outskirts%20of%20Sudzha%2C%20in%20the%20Kursk%20region%2C%20in%20August%202024.%3Cp%3EKIRILL%20CHUBOTIN%2FUkrinform%2FFuture%20Publishing%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGeorge%20Barros%2C%20the%20geospatial-intelligence%20team%20lead%20and%20a%20Russia%20analyst%20at%20ISW%2C%20said%20that%20the%20Kursk%20invasion%20underscores%20how%20Moscow%20left%20a%20major%20portion%20of%20its%20international%20border%20undefended.%20This%20leaves%20the%20Kremlin%20with%20a%20dilemma%3A%20does%20it%20continue%20to%20do%20this%20and%20risk%20more%20Ukrainian%20attacks%2C%20or%20does%20it%20move%20its%20forces%20to%20protect%20its%20borders%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20Kremlin%20goes%20with%20the%20latter%2C%20then%20that%20would%20drastically%20increase%20the%20resourcing%20requirements%20for%20Vladimir%20Putin%20to%20support%20and%20wage%20this%20protracted%20war%20of%20his%20indefinitely%2C%26quot%3B%20Barros%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20highlighting%20the%20challenges%20for%20the%20Russian%20president.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20a%20trivial%20requirement%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20combat%20power%20would%20either%20hail%20from%20Russia's%20operations%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20stripping%20it%20of%20resources%20there%2C%20or%20Russian%20society%2C%20as%20Moscow%20is%20forced%20to%20rely%20on%20conscription%20or%20a%20build-up%20of%20local%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20appears%20to%20already%20be%20looking%20for%20additional%20volunteer%20forces%20in%20Kursk%2C%20according%20to%20Britain's%20defense%20ministry%2C%20which%20said%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FDefenceHQ%2Fstatus%2F1829436257404874996%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eintelligence%20update%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20week%20that%20prospective%20recruits%20for%20this%20effort%20have%20been%20told%20they%20will%20serve%20only%20within%20that%20specific%20region%20on%20a%20short-term%20contract.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20the%20Kursk%20invasion%20may%20not%20be%20forcing%20Russia%20to%20redirect%20front-line%20forces%20from%20Pokrovsk%2C%20that%20campaign%20will%20eventually%20culminate.%20When%20it%20does%2C%20Barros%20said%2C%20Moscow%20will%20look%20to%20its%20forces%20in%20other%20areas%20as%20it%20pivots%20attention%20to%20another%20sector%20of%20the%20front%20line.%20At%20that%20point%2C%20the%20reshuffling%20of%20manpower%20could%20come%20into%20play.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223458%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20burning%20village%20in%20Russia's%20Kursk%20region%20with%20smoke%20rising%20up.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d745f214a5cd1fcc8cbbe9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221980%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20aerial%20view%20shows%20smoke%20erupting%20from%20a%20Russian%20building%20on%20fire%20following%20a%20Ukrainian%20military%20operation%20in%20Korenevo%2C%20in%20the%20Kursk%20region%2C%20in%20this%20screengrab%20taken%20from%20a%20handout%20video%20released%20on%20August%2029%2C%202024.%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBlack%20Swan%26quot%3B%20unit%20of%20the%20225%20Separate%20Assault%20Battalion%2FHandout%20via%20REUTERS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBarros%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20Kursk%20operation%20and%20the%20redeployment%20of%20those%2030%2C000%20troops%20are%20degrading%20the%20Russians'%20ability%20to%20plan%20for%20that%20contingency%20in%20the%20future.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20invasion%20of%20Kursk%20is%20also%20challenging%20the%20narrative%20that%20the%20war%20is%20a%20stalemate%20and%20that%20the%20situation%20can't%20improve%20for%20the%20Ukrainians%2C%20Barros%20said.%20This%20realization%20could%20prove%20important%20as%20the%20US%20presidential%20election%20%E2%80%94%20in%20which%20future%20military%20support%20for%20Kyiv%20hangs%20in%20the%20balance%20%E2%80%94%20draws%20closer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20unexpected%20invasion%20of%20Russia%20is%20a%20reminder%20to%20policymakers%20that%20the%20US%20plays%20an%20important%20role%20in%20the%20war%20and%20can%20influence%20the%20outcome%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20decisions%20about%20the%20rules%20of%20engagement%2C%20Barros%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20considerations%20are%20top%20concerns%20for%20Ukrainian%20officials%2C%20who%20have%20long%20pushed%20for%20the%20US%20to%20drop%20all%20restrictions%20on%20using%20American-provided%20weapons%20to%20strike%20military%20targets%20inside%20Russia.%20These%20efforts%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2024%2F08%2F23%2Fukraine-biden-weapons-restrictions-00176210%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eintensified%20since%20the%20start%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Kursk%20invasion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-kursk-invasion-russia-hasnt-eased-pressure-off-front-line-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725386468000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d744f414a5cd1fcc8cbb59%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-kursk-invasion-russia-hasnt-eased-pressure-off-front-line-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20month-old%20invasion%20of%20Russia's%20Kursk%20region%20has%20produced%20some%20positive%20effects%20for%20Ukraine%2C%20but%20one%20key%20goal%20hasn't%20been%20achieved%20yet.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jepstein%40businessinsider.com%20(Jake%20Epstein)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A34%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-kursk-invasion-russia-hasnt-eased-pressure-off-front-line-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Robert%20Zemeckis%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%98Here%E2%80%99%20Sets%20World%20Premiere%20AFI%20Fest%20%E2%80%93%20Film%20News%20in%20Brief%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725386400000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2Fhere_0444382_7.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1236128123%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Tuesday%2C%20Sept.%203%20The%20American%20Film%20Institute%20(AFI)%20announced%20the%20World%20Premiere%20of%20Robert%20Zemeckis%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%9CHere%E2%80%9D%20as%20th